  16. (* Pretty-printing of linearized machine code *)

  18. open Format
  19. open Mach
  20. open Printmach
  21. open Linear

  23. ‌let label ppf l =
  24.   Format.fprintf ppf "L%i" l

  26. ‌let instr ppf i =
  27.   begin match i.desc with
  28.   | Lend -> ()
  29.   | Lprologue ->
  30.       fprintf ppf "prologue"
  31.   | Lop op ->
  32.       begin match op with
  33.       | Ialloc _ | Ipoll _ | Icall_ind | Icall_imm _ | Iextcall _ ->
  34.           fprintf ppf "@[<1>{%a}@]@," regsetaddr i.live
  35.       | _ -> ()
  36.       end;
  37.       operation op i.arg ppf i.res
  38.   | Lreloadretaddr ->
  39.       fprintf ppf "reload retaddr"
  40.   | Lreturn ->
  41.       fprintf ppf "return %a" regs i.arg
  42.   | Llabel lbl ->
  43.       fprintf ppf "%a:" label lbl
  44.   | Lbranch lbl ->
  45.       fprintf ppf "goto %a" label lbl
  46.   | Lcondbranch(tst, lbl) ->
  47.       fprintf ppf "if %a goto %a" (test tst) i.arg label lbl
  48.   | Lcondbranch3(lbl0, lbl1, lbl2) ->
  49.       fprintf ppf "switch3 %a" reg i.arg.(0);
  50.       let case n = function
  51.       | None -> ()
  52.       | Some lbl ->
  53.          fprintf ppf "@,case %i: goto %a" n label lbl in
  54.       case 0 lbl0; case 1 lbl1; case 2 lbl2;
  55.       fprintf ppf "@,endswitch"
  56.   | Lswitch lblv ->
  57.       fprintf ppf "switch %a" reg i.arg.(0);
  58.       for i = 0 to Array.length lblv - 1 do
  59.        fprintf ppf "case %i: goto %a" i label lblv.(i)
  60.       done;
  61.       fprintf ppf "@,endswitch"
  62.   | Lentertrap ->
  63.       fprintf ppf "enter trap"
  64.   | Ladjust_trap_depth { delta_traps } ->
  65.       fprintf ppf "adjust trap depth by %d traps" delta_traps
  66.   | Lpushtrap { lbl_handler; } ->
  67.       fprintf ppf "push trap %a" label lbl_handler
  68.   | Lpoptrap ->
  69.       fprintf ppf "pop trap"
  70.   | Lraise k ->
  71.       fprintf ppf "%s %a" (Lambda.raise_kind k) reg i.arg.(0)
  72.   end;
  73.   if not (Debuginfo.is_none i.dbg) && !Clflags.locations then
  74.     fprintf ppf " %s" (Debuginfo.to_string i.dbg)

  76. ‌let rec all_instr ppf i =
  77.   match i.desc with
  78.   | Lend -> ()
  79.   | _ -> fprintf ppf "%a@,%a" instr i all_instr i.next

  81. ‌let fundecl ppf f =
  82.   let dbg =
  83.     if Debuginfo.is_none f.fun_dbg || not !Clflags.locations then
  84.       ""
  85.     else
  86.       " " ^ Debuginfo.to_string f.fun_dbg in
  87.   fprintf ppf "@[<v 2>%s:%s@,%a@]" f.fun_name dbg all_instr f.fun_body
